pasta.web.controller

Class CompetitionController

  • java.lang.Object
    • pasta.web.controller.CompetitionController

  • @Controller
@RequestMapping(value="competition/")
public class CompetitionController
extends java.lang.Object
    Controller class for Competition functions.

    Handles mappings of $PASTAUrl$/competition/...

    Both students and teaching staff can access this url. Students have highly limited functionality.

    Since:
    2013-08-15
    Version:
    2.0
    Author:
    Alex Radu

      • viewAllCompetitions

        @RequestMapping(value="")
public java.lang.String viewAllCompetitions(org.springframework.ui.Model model)
        $PASTAUrl$/competition/

        The landing page for competitions. Lists all competitions and shows how the user can interact with them. If the user has not authenticated: redirect to login. ATTRIBUTES:

        unikeyThe user object
        allCompetitionsThe collection of all competitions
        JSP:
        • assessment/viewAll/competition
        Parameters:
        model - the model being used
        Returns:
        "redirect:/login/" or "assessment/viewAll/competition"

      • newCompetition

                method=POST)
public java.lang.String newCompetition(org.springframework.ui.Model model,
                                             @ModelAttribute(value="newCompetitionModel")
                                             NewCompetition form)
        $PASTAUrl$/competition/ - POST

        Add a new competition If the user has not authenticated: redirect to login. If the user is not a tutor: redirect to home If the user is an Instructor: add the competition using CompetitionManager.addCompetition(NewCompetition) redirect to mirror

        Parameters:
        model - the model being used
        form - the new competition form
        Returns:
        "redirect:/login" or "redirect:/home/" or "redirect:/mirror/"

      • updateCompetition

        @RequestMapping(value="{competitionName}/",
                method=POST)
public java.lang.String updateCompetition(@ModelAttribute(value="newCompetitionModel")
                                                NewCompetition form,
                                                @ModelAttribute(value="competition")
                                                Competition compForm,
                                                @PathVariable(value="competitionName")
                                                java.lang.String competitionName,
                                                org.springframework.ui.Model model)
        $PASTAUrl$/competition/{competitionName}/ - POST

        Update a competition If the user has not authenticated: redirect to login. If the user is not a tutor: redirect to home. If the user is an instructor: Update the competition based on which form was submitted using either CompetitionManager.updateCompetition(Competition) or CompetitionManager.updateCompetition(NewCompetition)

        Parameters:
        form - the new competition form (used when changing code)
        compForm - the competition to be updated (used when changing competition information and not code)
        competitionName - the short name (no whitespace) of the competition
        model - the model being used
        Returns:
        "redirect:/login/" or "redirect:/home/" or "redirect:."

      • viewCompetitionPage

        @RequestMapping(value="view/{competitionName}/")
public java.lang.String viewCompetitionPage(org.springframework.ui.Model model,
                                                  @PathVariable(value="competitionName")
                                                  java.lang.String competitionName)
        $PASTAUrl/competition/view/{competitionName}/

        View the competition page. Differs based on if the competition is calculated or arena based. If the user has not authenticated: redirect to login. If the user is not a tutor and the competition isn't live: redirect to home. ATTRIBUTES:

        unikeythe user object of the currently logged in user
        competitionthe competition object
        arenaResultthe results of the last execution if it's a calculated competition. I know it's called arenaResult, I was lazy and copy-pasting is fun.
        marksThe mars awarded to the users based on their performance
        JSP:
        • assessment/competition/calculated - if it's a calculated competition
        • assessment/competition/arena - if it's an arena based competition
        Parameters:
        model - the model being used
        competitionName - the short name (no whitespace) of the competition
        Returns:
        "redirect:/login/" or "redirect:/home/" or "assessment/competition/calculated" or "assessment/competition/arena"

      • addArena

        @RequestMapping(value="view/{competitionName}/",
                method=POST)
public java.lang.String addArena(org.springframework.ui.Model model,
                                       @ModelAttribute(value="newArenaModel")
                                       Arena arena,
                                       @PathVariable(value="competitionName")
                                       java.lang.String competitionName)
        $PASTAUrl$/competition/view/{competitionName}/ - POST

        Add an arena to a competition If the user has not authenticated: redirect to login. If the user is not a tutor and the competition isn't live: redirect to home. If the arena has a valid name (is only alphanumeric characters) and the competition is not calculated and the competition allows the user to create an arena, then add the arena using CompetitionManager.addArena(Arena, Competition)

        Parameters:
        model - the model being used
        arena - the arena being added
        competitionName - the short name (no whitespace) of the competition
        Returns:
        "redirect:/login/" or "redirect:/home/" or "redirect:/mirror/"

      • viewArenaPage

        @RequestMapping(value="view/{competitionName}/{arenaName}/")
public java.lang.String viewArenaPage(org.springframework.ui.Model model,
                                            @PathVariable(value="arenaName")
                                            java.lang.String arenaName,
                                            @PathVariable(value="competitionName")
                                            java.lang.String competitionName)
        $PASTAUrl$/competition/view/{competitionName}/{arenaName}/

        View the details on an arena. If the user has not authenticated: redirect to login. If the user is not a tutor and the competition isn't live: redirect to home. If the competition is calculated: redirect to the competition page. Otherwise: add attributes and serve up jsp ATTRIBUTES:

        unikeyThe user object for the currently logged in user
        playersA list of players the currently logged in user has uploaded and are not retired
        arenathe arena object
        completeda flag for whether the arena has finished executing and will not execute again
        resultsthe results object (ArenaResult)
        officiala flag for whether the arena is the official arena or not
        JSP:
        • assessment/competition/arenaDetails
        Parameters:
        model - the model being used
        arenaName - the name of the arena.
        competitionName - the short name (no whitespace) of the competition
        Returns:
        "redirect:/login/" or "redirect:/home/" or "redirect:../" or "assessment/competition/arenaDetails"

      • submitNewPlayer

        @RequestMapping(value="{competitionName}/myPlayers/",
                method=POST)
public java.lang.String submitNewPlayer(org.springframework.ui.Model model,
                                              @PathVariable(value="competitionName")
                                              java.lang.String competitionName,
                                              @ModelAttribute(value="newPlayerModel")
                                              NewPlayer playerForm,
                                              org.springframework.validation.BindingResult result)
        $PASTAUrl$/competition/{competitionName}/myPlayers/" - POST

        Submit a player. If the user has not authenticated: redirect to login. If the user is not a tutor and the competition isn't live: redirect to home. Validate the player using CompetitionManager.addPlayer(NewPlayer, String, String, BindingResult), if the player fails validation, give the feedback to the user. ATTRIBUTES:

        unikeythe user object of the currently logged in player
        competitionthe competition object
        nodeListthe collection of nodes for the root of the folder structure of the code of the players uploaded, will only be use by tutors atm.
        playersthe list of all of the players that have been uploaded for this competition by this player
        JSP:
        • assessment/competition/players
        Parameters:
        model - the model being used
        competitionName - the short name (no whitespace) of the competition
        playerForm - the new player form containing the code
        result - the binding result used for feedback.
        Returns:
        "redirect:/login/" or "redirect:/home/" or "redirect:/mirror/" or "assessment/competition/players"

      • viewOthersPlayers

        $PASTAUrl$/competition/view/{competitionName}/{unikey}/players/

        View another user's list of players. If the user has not authenticated: redirect to login. If the user is not a tutor and the competition isn't live or the viewed user doesn't exist: redirect to home. ATTRIBUTES:

        "redirect:/login/" or "redirect:/home/" or "assessment/competition/players"
